replies.body:
{{champion:29}} 

Will be strong in the jungle meta and abuse his  stealth for lane ganks that basically force flashes or kills early game. His w change also gives him decent single target and aoe clear speeds. 

Item wise he'll prob start getting things like{{item:1419}} {{item:3085}} with {{item:3031}}  or {{item:3072}}  

{{champion:107}} {{champion:121}} 
Probably going to be perma ban for a while. -_- Sadly these are  the 2 assassins that I want to play when the patch hits. New Rengar looks like he could pull off a hellacious bruiser build. Kha'zix evolution changes are cool but really don't fulfill the goal of providing choices (Still going to be a set pattern for nearly all situations).

{{champion:55}} 
Picks are prob going to be a bunch of feeders / do horrible from the number of players used to her kit having a ridiculously low skill floor. The rework is adding extra mechanics to a champion that is notorious for being easy to play and *hard*  to play well.

{{champion:105}} 
His max range ult seems to be a bit too big right now.

{{champion:202}} 
Is going to have a lower pick / win rate and he'll prob start grabbing things like {{item:3053}} {{item:3072}} {{item:3812}} {{item:3046}} {{item:3026}} in his build. Other adcs will probably start trending towards those items to counter the upsurge in assassins  that will happen at the start of the season . Adcs will be posting complaint threads again due to be in the hell meta for adc.

{{item:3026}} 
Is probably going to be changed. Especially since it has had a giant upsurge of people building it after the 60 minute hell matches in worlds.

{{champion:127}} {{champion:6}} {{champion:10}} {{champion:31}} {{champion:57}} 
These champions alongside tank supports are going to be played more often. They're generally good in assassin metas. 

{{item:3147}} {{item:3142}} 

Are going to probably fall out of marksman builds or at least the ghost blade will. Lethality doesn't become equivalent to current armor pen until something like level 8 for dirk, 18 for ghost blade, and is better for duskblade by the time you buy it. The loss of +atkspd on the ghostblade active makes it purely for the movespeed so it might still help out low mobility champs (Not nearly as attractive without the extra %atkspd and scaling time on 20 lethality).

Edge of night is  going to be abused on anything that likes ad / lethality and is a heavy nerf to cc if it keeps being a 30s morgana spellshield with a small cast time. It will get nerfed or adjusted a lot.

Redemption will quickly become annoying and sexy.

Knights vow is going to be a rush item on {{champion:412}} {{champion:201}} {{champion:12}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:54}} {{champion:57}{{champion:89}}{{champion:57}}{{champion:111}}   and is going to be op if it is released how it is on pbe.

{{champion:111}} 
Mains of this champion are going to have a good time.  He's a good flex pick and pretty strong into a lot of the champions that will be meta. Plus he can build redemption in all three of his lanes (Top, Support, Jng)
